The paper deals with interference management in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas and beamforming techniques suggests a possible fit with the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the joint optimization of the physical and medium access control layers could also be relevant to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, which deals with the design of intelligent systems.
